WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:14.014 --> 00:00:16.433
Why is it taking so long
to get our system back online?

3
00:00:18.227 --> 00:00:19.269
There'll be reasons.

4
00:00:20.646 --> 00:00:22.022
Well. that's rather defeatist. isn't it?

5
00:00:22.105 --> 00:00:23.774
We're supposed to be impregnable.

6
00:00:24.358 --> 00:00:25.526
I have three questions.

7
00:00:25.609 --> 00:00:29.238
How. why. what the living fuck is next?
And no answers.

8
00:00:29.321 --> 00:00:30.739
Afraid heads are gonna have to roll.

9
00:00:31.949 --> 00:00:32.950
Fuck.

10
00:00:39.873 --> 00:00:40.874
Why is there a countdown?

11
00:00:40.958 --> 00:00:44.628
It just appeared.
We don't know why. Not the best answer.

12
00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:45.963
Well. it's not an answer.

13
00:00:47.339 --> 00:00:51.552
Isn't there some kind of anti…
antivirus software

14
00:00:51.635 --> 00:00:54.638
that you can use.
or maybe like a backdoor patch?

15
00:00:54.721 --> 00:00:56.557
I don't think shouting out random words

16
00:00:56.640 --> 00:00:58.600
you found at the bottom of emails
is going to help.

17
00:00:59.184 --> 00:01:00.519
Thanks.

18
00:01:00.602 --> 00:01:03.397
Okay. okay. Duncan. What about a reboot?

19
00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:05.147
What. you mean turn it off and on again?

20
00:01:05.232 --> 00:01:06.608
No.

21
00:01:07.484 --> 00:01:10.279
Unless that would work. If we do that.
would that be any good at all?

22
00:01:10.362 --> 00:01:12.739
You can't turn it off.
They can't do anything right now.

23
00:01:12.823 --> 00:01:14.700
Claude. why don't we give them some space?

24
00:01:18.871 --> 00:01:21.039
You should never have inputted
that code she gave you.

25
00:01:21.123 --> 00:01:22.958
You should never have let her
leave the building.

26
00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:24.835
I was only trying to
stop Libyan terrorists

27
00:01:24.918 --> 00:01:26.503
from rampaging
through the fucking capital.

28
00:01:26.587 --> 00:01:28.714
She wanted you to let her go.

29
00:01:28.797 --> 00:01:31.592
What are you talking about?
She… She was terrified.

30
00:01:31.675 --> 00:01:33.343
I had to convince her. I…

31
00:01:33.427 --> 00:01:36.138
When Ho allowed her
to access the database.

32
00:01:36.221 --> 00:01:38.390
she stole your file. Claude.

33
00:01:38.473 --> 00:01:42.311
She played you. You've been profiled.
You've been honey-trapped.

34
00:01:45.355 --> 00:01:46.773
You and me both. bro.

35
00:01:47.441 --> 00:01:48.692
You didn't stand a chance.

36
00:01:49.484 --> 00:01:51.528
She's a female me.
That's why I fell in love with her.

37
00:01:53.906 --> 00:01:56.658
Okay. good news. bad news.

38
00:01:56.742 --> 00:01:59.036
There is a way to reverse
whatever they've done…

39
00:01:59.119 --> 00:02:00.120
Great.

40
00:02:00.204 --> 00:02:01.705
…but not before the countdown ends.

41
00:02:02.664 --> 00:02:03.999
I'm so embarrassed for you.

42
00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:06.084
- Sir.
- Yeah?

43
00:02:06.168 --> 00:02:07.836
The Libyan ambassador's on line one.

44
00:02:07.920 --> 00:02:10.506
In his own time.
I only made the call fucking hours ago.

45
00:02:10.589 --> 00:02:11.798
Thank you.

46
00:02:11.882 --> 00:02:12.883
Thank you.

47
00:02:18.972 --> 00:02:20.682
- Ambassador.
- Mr. Whelan.

48
00:02:22.976 --> 00:02:26.271
My sincere apologies on behalf
of the Libyan government.

49
00:02:27.064 --> 00:02:31.401
I have just been made aware that
a dissident group of security operatives

50
00:02:31.485 --> 00:02:34.571
are responsible for the terrible events

51
00:02:34.655 --> 00:02:36.406
of the last few days.

52
00:02:36.490 --> 00:02:38.450
Yes. well. I'm sure that we can trust you

53
00:02:38.534 --> 00:02:41.078
to do your very best to help us find them.

54
00:02:41.870 --> 00:02:43.622
You can speak to one of them now.

55
00:02:44.665 --> 00:02:45.666
What. sorry?

56
00:02:53.465 --> 00:02:55.926
This is the vulnerable young woman
you spoke to earlier.

57
00:02:56.760 --> 00:02:59.555
Remember? You were right.

58
00:02:59.638 --> 00:03:01.306
I am stronger than I thought.

59
00:03:01.390 --> 00:03:04.643
with reserves of strength
I was not even aware of.

60
00:03:04.726 --> 00:03:05.853
Who the hell are you really?

61
00:03:05.936 --> 00:03:09.773
Someone who grew up in a country
ruined by your arrogant intervention.

62
00:03:10.732 --> 00:03:12.276
You left us with years of horror.

63
00:03:12.359 --> 00:03:15.821
Nothing can justify your slaughter
of 11 people.

64
00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:18.031
I need to speak to someone in authority.

65
00:03:18.115 --> 00:03:19.950
Guess what?
You're speaking to the head of MI5.

66
00:03:20.033 --> 00:03:21.410
Yes. I know.

67
00:03:21.493 --> 00:03:23.620
You kept telling me
when I was a trembling girl

68
00:03:23.704 --> 00:03:25.163
you were trying to impress.

69
00:03:26.164 --> 00:03:29.751
And since then.
we shut down your computer system

70
00:03:29.835 --> 00:03:31.712
and humiliated your leadership.

71
00:03:32.880 --> 00:03:35.424
Yeah. I guess we could say
we blinded our enemies.

72
00:03:36.425 --> 00:03:38.010
Put Diana Taverner on.

73
00:03:41.138 --> 00:03:42.139
Taverner.

74
00:03:43.348 --> 00:03:45.684
Unless you give in to our demands.

75
00:03:45.767 --> 00:03:48.020
when the countdown on your screen ends.

76
00:03:48.103 --> 00:03:50.856
the final item
on the destabilization strategy…

77
00:03:50.939 --> 00:03:55.777
you know. the one created by you
and inflicted on many of your colonies…

78
00:03:56.361 --> 00:03:57.613
will be carried out.

79
00:03:57.696 --> 00:03:59.948
What are your demands?

80
00:04:00.032 --> 00:04:01.783
£100 million.

81
00:04:01.867 --> 00:04:04.203
Compensation for years
of lost oil revenues

82
00:04:04.286 --> 00:04:08.123
to be paid into a Cayman Island trust
called Albion Holdings.

83
00:04:09.166 --> 00:04:11.293
Which is a fraction of what we are owed.

84
00:04:11.960 --> 00:04:13.462
Call me when you have it.

85
00:04:18.132 --> 00:04:20.219
Relax. You'll get out when we're paid.

86
00:04:21.512 --> 00:04:22.513
Bye.

87
00:04:24.640 --> 00:04:26.850
They want 100 million
before that countdown ends.

88
00:04:26.934 --> 00:04:29.645
or they will carry out
the remaining action on their list.

89
00:04:29.728 --> 00:04:31.980
What's the last action on the list?

90
00:04:32.064 --> 00:04:33.315
Attack a place of worship.

91
00:04:33.398 --> 00:04:36.068
Right. But it's-it's Sunday morning.

92
00:04:36.151 --> 00:04:38.987
Jesus fucking Christ.
How are we gonna find them?

93
00:06:20.506 --> 00:06:21.507
Diana.

94
00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:23.008
We lost Tara.

95
00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:26.178
You knew she'd play Whelan. didn't you?

96
00:06:26.261 --> 00:06:28.055
I had my suspicions.

97
00:06:29.014 --> 00:06:31.266
Which were confirmed once I read his file.

98
00:06:31.350 --> 00:06:35.395
His psych profile screams
"daddy savior complex."

99
00:06:36.063 --> 00:06:39.650
I'd have given you a call.
but I thought you'd enjoy watching him

100
00:06:39.733 --> 00:06:42.236
make a complete and utter
fucking tit of himself.

101
00:06:43.820 --> 00:06:45.531
They issued any demands yet?

102
00:06:46.114 --> 00:06:47.950
She just called from the embassy.

103
00:06:48.033 --> 00:06:50.494
Free passage and 100 million
in lost oil revenue.

104
00:06:51.954 --> 00:06:54.414
Well. they might have a point
about our behavior.

105
00:06:55.332 --> 00:06:57.417
but they trousered most of their oil money

106
00:06:57.501 --> 00:06:59.711
and spent the change
keeping their people down.

107
00:07:00.838 --> 00:07:04.550
They've crashed our systems
and given us an hour. which ends at 10:06.

108
00:07:05.175 --> 00:07:07.010
Otherwise they attack a place of worship.

109
00:07:07.094 --> 00:07:08.387
Sunday morning.

110
00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:10.138
They've timed it well.

111
00:07:11.890 --> 00:07:14.309
I guess you're just gonna have to
pay the money.

112
00:07:25.320 --> 00:07:26.655
Ma'am.

113
00:07:26.738 --> 00:07:28.740
There are around 2.000 churches
across London.

114
00:07:28.824 --> 00:07:31.994
If you add in mosques. synagogues.
temples and multifaith centers.

115
00:07:32.786 --> 00:07:35.330
we're looking at over 5.000
potential targets.

116
00:07:36.123 --> 00:07:39.751
Yes. but Muslims don't worship
on a Sunday.

117
00:07:42.045 --> 00:07:43.505
I'm right in thinking that. aren't I?

118
00:07:44.381 --> 00:07:45.549
Well. I'm Sikh.

119
00:07:47.801 --> 00:07:49.761
Well let's assume it's churches. shall we?

120
00:07:49.845 --> 00:07:52.890
High-value targets.
St. Paul's. Westminster Abbey.

121
00:07:52.973 --> 00:07:54.474
They already have protection.

122
00:07:54.558 --> 00:07:57.728
If we throw everything at St. Paul's.
and the attack happens elsewhere.

123
00:07:57.811 --> 00:08:00.981
it'll look like we were rushing to protect
the landmarks rather than the people.

124
00:08:01.064 --> 00:08:02.232
Okay. We shut 'em all down.

125
00:08:02.316 --> 00:08:05.569
And how are we gonna get people
to stay away from every London church

126
00:08:05.652 --> 00:08:08.155
in the next 40 minutes?
There'll be absolute chaos.

127
00:08:08.238 --> 00:08:09.489
Call in the Met.

128
00:08:10.073 --> 00:08:12.117
We don't have enough armed police.

129
00:08:12.201 --> 00:08:13.577
Okay. then we call in the army.

130
00:08:14.494 --> 00:08:15.621
In 40 minutes?

131
00:08:15.704 --> 00:08:18.081
Ma'am. the Treasury have verified

132
00:08:18.165 --> 00:08:20.083
the Cayman Island trust
where the money's to be paid.

133
00:08:20.667 --> 00:08:21.960
It's linked to this company.

134
00:08:25.464 --> 00:08:27.674
Jesus Christ. Right. Get him in.

135
00:08:27.758 --> 00:08:29.551
- He's already on his way.
- Keep him out of sight.

136
00:08:29.635 --> 00:08:31.512
I'm sorry. why are we checking
where they want the money sent?

137
00:08:31.595 --> 00:08:32.596
We're not gonna pay it.

138
00:08:32.679 --> 00:08:34.389
I think we should have the option.

139
00:08:35.474 --> 00:08:38.018
You need to call the PM now.
Get it cleared.

140
00:08:38.769 --> 00:08:40.854
Give in to terror? He won't hear of it.

141
00:08:40.938 --> 00:08:43.941
Well. then. you are looking
at a second Abbotsfield.

142
00:08:48.320 --> 00:08:50.072
Send the Dogs down to the Libyan embassy.

143
00:08:50.155 --> 00:08:54.284
If this goes without bloodshed. we shall
escort her and her team to the airport.

144
00:08:54.368 --> 00:08:57.454
If it goes the other way. I want them
to be ready to storm the building.

145
00:09:01.083 --> 00:09:02.960
Shouldn't we be. you know. doing things.

146
00:09:03.043 --> 00:09:06.839
like trying to track the Libyans
or-or-or Roddy's girlfriend?

147
00:09:06.922 --> 00:09:08.549
She's at the Libyan embassy.

148
00:09:08.632 --> 00:09:10.300
What. so it was a state-sanctioned op?

149
00:09:10.384 --> 00:09:12.636
No. I doubt that.

150
00:09:13.220 --> 00:09:15.138
She forced her way in there
'cause she knows

151
00:09:15.222 --> 00:09:17.224
that we can't go in and drag her out.

152
00:09:22.521 --> 00:09:23.689
That Grandpa?

153
00:09:23.772 --> 00:09:26.233
No. Yes. How did you know that?

154
00:09:26.316 --> 00:09:30.070
Well. if it was of operational relevance.
you would've taken it.

155
00:09:30.153 --> 00:09:31.989
and you've got no personal life
so it must be him.

156
00:09:32.072 --> 00:09:33.699
H-How's he doing. by the way?

157
00:09:34.533 --> 00:09:36.285
Not great. no.

158
00:09:36.368 --> 00:09:38.203
He's picking up
on what's happening from the news.

159
00:09:38.287 --> 00:09:39.746
but he's getting it slightly jumbled.

160
00:09:39.830 --> 00:09:41.623
- Don't say anything.
- About what?

161
00:09:41.707 --> 00:09:43.667
About him getting confused. okay?

162
00:09:43.750 --> 00:09:46.253
I know that you two had your differences.
but just leave it there.

163
00:09:46.336 --> 00:09:48.714
He was the sharpest mind
in the building. After me.

164
00:09:48.797 --> 00:09:50.507
Now you're gonna say something horrible.

165
00:09:50.591 --> 00:09:52.718
Something unutterably vile about him

166
00:09:52.801 --> 00:09:54.887
being an embarrassing shadow
of his former self.

167
00:09:54.970 --> 00:09:56.597
I don't have to. You just said it for me.

168
00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:58.557
- This isn't helping.
- I--

169
00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:00.142
What are we going to do?

170
00:10:00.225 --> 00:10:01.518
And don't say. "nothing."

171
00:10:03.103 --> 00:10:04.563
There's nothing to do.

172
00:10:04.646 --> 00:10:06.899
These guys are bloody good
and they're fucking ruthless.

173
00:10:06.982 --> 00:10:09.902
The Park can't protect
every church in London.

174
00:10:09.985 --> 00:10:12.070
Well. then they will have
to pay the money.

175
00:10:12.154 --> 00:10:14.781
- And what happens if they don't?
- Then there'd be a massacre.

176
00:10:14.865 --> 00:10:16.825
At a random church in London?

177
00:10:16.909 --> 00:10:18.827
- This is a nightmare.
- Maybe not that random.

178
00:10:18.911 --> 00:10:21.496
There is one place of worship
I can think of.

179
00:10:22.456 --> 00:10:26.543
Although. it would only occur to
a complete and utter fucking psychopath.

180
00:10:33.592 --> 00:10:34.968
You think he knows which one?

181
00:10:36.762 --> 00:10:37.763
Shit.

182
00:10:39.556 --> 00:10:41.308
Wait. w-where are they going?

183
00:10:41.391 --> 00:10:42.559
Abbotsfield.

184
00:10:42.643 --> 00:10:44.728
Abbotsfi… There's already been
an attack at Abbotsfield.

185
00:10:44.811 --> 00:10:48.357
Which they are commemorating
at a multifaith center shortly.

186
00:10:50.192 --> 00:10:54.613
You can't just say shit like that
and then just sit there and do nothing.

187
00:10:54.696 --> 00:10:57.783
I'm not doing nothing.
I'm sending my best agents.

188
00:10:58.534 --> 00:10:59.618
And you.

189
00:11:07.543 --> 00:11:09.086
May I ask why I've been summoned here

190
00:11:09.169 --> 00:11:11.672
then made to wait on the stairs
like a member of staff?

191
00:11:12.339 --> 00:11:14.216
When you came to visit me the other night.

192
00:11:14.299 --> 00:11:17.177
you mentioned a group of
disaffected Libyans wanting compensation

193
00:11:17.261 --> 00:11:18.804
for lost oil revenues.

194
00:11:18.887 --> 00:11:23.100
As of now. we have 25 minutes
to pay up 100 million

195
00:11:23.183 --> 00:11:27.354
to stop a Libyan group
from attacking a church.

196
00:11:28.313 --> 00:11:29.773
I have no knowledge of any of this.

197
00:11:30.858 --> 00:11:32.276
It's an extremely fractured country.

198
00:11:32.359 --> 00:11:34.987
and in my limited experience.
every fucker you meet is on the take.

199
00:11:35.070 --> 00:11:37.739
The people you're dealing with may be
part of a completely separate group.

200
00:11:37.823 --> 00:11:42.744
The payment has to go to an offshore trust
where you are a director.

201
00:11:44.413 --> 00:11:47.416
In that case. fuck. shit. bugger and yes.
it seems it is the same people.

202
00:11:47.499 --> 00:11:49.626
I will never do business
in the Middle East again.

203
00:11:49.710 --> 00:11:50.752
They love to haggle.

204
00:11:50.836 --> 00:11:53.172
and they have a tendency
to go completely fucking crackers.

205
00:11:53.255 --> 00:11:54.590
Why do they have your details?

206
00:11:55.757 --> 00:11:56.967
There are two accounts.

207
00:11:57.509 --> 00:12:02.181
One to distribute funds to them
once they've come in. minus my commission.

208
00:12:02.264 --> 00:12:03.849
Nothing in that one at the moment.
obviously.

209
00:12:03.932 --> 00:12:04.933
And the other?

210
00:12:06.018 --> 00:12:09.563
They've paid me a nominal fee
for the last three years.

211
00:12:09.646 --> 00:12:12.065
Recently they intimated
I wasn't doing enough.

212
00:12:12.149 --> 00:12:14.693
- hence my visit to you.
- And when you say "nominal." you mean…

213
00:12:14.776 --> 00:12:17.487
All told. a couple of hundred grand.

214
00:12:18.155 --> 00:12:19.990
Which I will declare in due course.

215
00:12:20.073 --> 00:12:21.575
Why are they dragging me
into this insanity?

216
00:12:21.658 --> 00:12:22.659
It makes me look terrible.

217
00:12:22.743 --> 00:12:25.370
Because you took their money
and did nothing and they want to show

218
00:12:25.454 --> 00:12:27.539
what a corrupt mess this country is.

219
00:12:28.373 --> 00:12:30.959
Getting paid through
the former Home Secretary

220
00:12:31.043 --> 00:12:32.628
is a very good way of doing it.

221
00:12:34.046 --> 00:12:36.715
When this comes out.
we will all look terrible.

222
00:12:41.011 --> 00:12:42.137
Prime Minister.

223
00:12:42.221 --> 00:12:45.849
I'm afraid it's highly unlikely the attack
can be prevented without paying.

224
00:12:46.433 --> 00:12:48.769
No. No. I'm as disappointed as you are.

225
00:12:57.402 --> 00:12:58.487
Twelve minutes. sir.

226
00:12:59.780 --> 00:13:01.615
Well. Taverner's left us with no choice.

227
00:13:02.866 --> 00:13:03.867
Mmm.

228
00:13:04.910 --> 00:13:06.703
They didn't give us an hour
to stop the killing.

229
00:13:06.787 --> 00:13:08.497
They gave us an hour to find the money.

230
00:13:08.580 --> 00:13:10.165
We have been outplayed.

231
00:13:29.560 --> 00:13:33.772
We will pay. But I want your word
the attack will be called off.

232
00:13:35.566 --> 00:13:38.318
And I want your word
we'll be allowed to leave the country.

233
00:13:38.402 --> 00:13:42.990
Cars will be arriving shortly.
ready to take you to RAF Northolt.

234
00:13:43.073 --> 00:13:47.828
But safe passage is only guaranteed
if you and all your team leave

235
00:13:47.911 --> 00:13:50.247
to ensure there is no further violence.

236
00:13:52.416 --> 00:13:55.210
And also. none of this ever comes out.

237
00:13:56.712 --> 00:13:58.589
I can imagine
you must feel humiliated. huh?

238
00:14:00.257 --> 00:14:01.717
Unpleasant. isn't it?

239
00:14:01.800 --> 00:14:03.802
Do you agree to our terms?

240
00:14:03.886 --> 00:14:06.805
I'll stand them down. and they will
return to the embassy shortly.

241
00:14:06.889 --> 00:14:09.349
Any more violence.
and those men in the cars

242
00:14:09.433 --> 00:14:11.101
will not be taking you to the airport.

243
00:14:11.185 --> 00:14:13.187
They will be taking you down.

244
00:14:13.979 --> 00:14:15.981
There'll be no more violence.

245
00:14:16.982 --> 00:14:18.275
Transfer authorized.

246
00:14:32.289 --> 00:14:33.415
So I see.

247
00:14:41.590 --> 00:14:44.051
They paid. We did it.

248
00:14:44.134 --> 00:14:47.012
Get back to the embassy.
They're going to fly us out of here.

249
00:14:47.679 --> 00:14:49.306
You're starting to believe your role.

250
00:14:49.389 --> 00:14:50.599
You're a recruit.

251
00:14:50.682 --> 00:14:52.392
Not the one who gives orders.

252
00:14:54.645 --> 00:14:55.854
What are you talking about?

253
00:14:55.938 --> 00:14:57.147
It's over.

254
00:14:57.231 --> 00:14:58.815
Not for us.

255
00:14:59.858 --> 00:15:00.859
Listen.

256
00:15:02.027 --> 00:15:05.364
If you do anything else.
they're going to storm the building.

257
00:15:16.458 --> 00:15:17.668
Get ready.

258
00:15:20.754 --> 00:15:21.755
Did they pay?

259
00:15:22.339 --> 00:15:23.340
So?

260
00:15:23.966 --> 00:15:25.467
Why should that stop us?

261
00:15:27.135 --> 00:15:28.136
And this?

262
00:15:28.846 --> 00:15:30.764
What about this? Huh?

263
00:15:31.890 --> 00:15:33.600
I want them to pay in blood.

264
00:15:34.393 --> 00:15:36.186
like the blood I saw spilled.

265
00:15:37.312 --> 00:15:39.147
They smashed our country
then went back to their lives.

266
00:15:39.231 --> 00:15:40.399
leaving us with the horror of war.

267
00:15:40.482 --> 00:15:42.359
They must feel the same horror.

268
00:15:43.235 --> 00:15:46.405
Maybe next time they will think twice
before they start a war and walk away.

269
00:15:53.328 --> 00:15:55.414
- Where the fuck are you going?
- Look.

270
00:15:55.497 --> 00:15:57.791
You pick your target.
and I will pick mine.

271
00:15:58.584 --> 00:16:00.252
Guys. enough innocents have died.

272
00:16:00.335 --> 00:16:02.796
The last blow should fall on the people
that caused the war.

273
00:16:06.258 --> 00:16:08.510
I'm only going to spill the blood
of the guilty.

274
00:16:09.136 --> 00:16:10.679
As justice for my family.

275
00:16:13.515 --> 00:16:14.516
What about you?

276
00:16:16.518 --> 00:16:17.561
Come on. bro.

277
00:16:32.910 --> 00:16:35.495
Don't know how you can eat
at a time like this.

278
00:16:42.794 --> 00:16:43.879
Is that vegan?

279
00:16:44.838 --> 00:16:46.048
No. I asked for meat.

280
00:16:47.549 --> 00:16:49.676
Yeah. but if that was meat.
it would be bright pink.

281
00:16:51.178 --> 00:16:52.429
Sausage rolls got a…

282
00:16:52.513 --> 00:16:54.014
Yes. all right.

283
00:16:56.683 --> 00:17:01.355
If you were coming out of that building.
trying to lose the Dogs.

284
00:17:02.523 --> 00:17:03.690
which direction would you head?

285
00:17:03.774 --> 00:17:05.400
Do you think Tara's going
to try and escape?

286
00:17:05.483 --> 00:17:06.734
Answer the question.

287
00:17:11.031 --> 00:17:13.157
Left. Left down that alley.

288
00:17:13.242 --> 00:17:16.494
You said that they'll all get free passage
out of the country

289
00:17:16.578 --> 00:17:18.288
if she calls off this attack.

290
00:17:19.289 --> 00:17:20.582
Well. she's just a kid.

291
00:17:21.750 --> 00:17:23.502
There's no way she's running the show.

292
00:17:24.752 --> 00:17:26.713
Yes. her men should've been
back here by now.

293
00:17:28.006 --> 00:17:29.758
I don't think they're coming back.

294
00:17:30.843 --> 00:17:32.678
I think she's sitting in there

295
00:17:33.512 --> 00:17:36.807
realizing she never was in control
of her band of psychos.

296
00:17:36.890 --> 00:17:38.475
But you said we're paying the money.

297
00:17:38.559 --> 00:17:42.312
Well. look at what these guys have
got up to in the last couple of days.

298
00:17:42.396 --> 00:17:45.816
And I don't think money is gonna
quell their rage.

299
00:17:49.611 --> 00:17:51.280
Now Dogs are going in.

300
00:17:52.322 --> 00:17:56.076
But innocent people could get caught
in the cross fire.

301
00:17:56.702 --> 00:18:01.290
Yeah. they're in more danger
from our trigger-happy muscle

302
00:18:01.373 --> 00:18:02.499
than they are from her.

303
00:18:02.583 --> 00:18:04.209
We can't just sit here.

304
00:18:07.004 --> 00:18:08.714
- Well. go on then.
- What?

305
00:18:10.382 --> 00:18:12.134
Go and knock on the door.

306
00:18:12.217 --> 00:18:13.468
What? Me?

307
00:18:14.553 --> 00:18:17.931
Yesterday. you physically assaulted
the mayor.

308
00:18:18.015 --> 00:18:19.850
I don't know why you're
getting your knickers in a twist

309
00:18:19.933 --> 00:18:21.059
about knocking on a door.

310
00:18:21.143 --> 00:18:22.603
Yesterday. I had no choice.

311
00:18:22.686 --> 00:18:26.398
Bollocks. You get a real thrill
from being in the action.

312
00:18:27.441 --> 00:18:29.985
Probably it reminds you
of the rush you used to get

313
00:18:30.068 --> 00:18:31.820
when you got absolutely arseholed.

314
00:18:34.448 --> 00:18:36.491
Well. what am I doing
after I knock on the door?

315
00:18:37.492 --> 00:18:39.244
Telling her to follow you.

316
00:18:39.328 --> 00:18:41.246
Unless she wants to get shot in the head.

317
00:18:42.206 --> 00:18:47.252
They're not gonna shoot her out here.
unarmed in the street.

318
00:18:47.336 --> 00:18:50.088
It's a different story
if they go in the building.

319
00:18:50.172 --> 00:18:51.298
And like you said.

320
00:18:52.466 --> 00:18:55.594
- innocent people could get hurt.
- Guess I did say that. didn't I?

321
00:18:57.930 --> 00:19:01.600
That's it. They won't look twice
at a harmless little old lady.

322
00:19:02.643 --> 00:19:03.644
Cool.

323
00:19:19.993 --> 00:19:21.537
Sorry. ma'am. Embassy's closed.

324
00:19:21.620 --> 00:19:23.664
No. it's all right. I have an appointment.

325
00:19:25.082 --> 00:19:27.876
- Ma'am. you are not allowed to be here.
- Who are you?

326
00:19:27.960 --> 00:19:29.461
Yes. I'm MI5. let me in.

327
00:19:29.545 --> 00:19:31.004
Step back from the building. please.

328
00:19:31.088 --> 00:19:33.173
Let me in nicely or men
with guns are coming in.

329
00:19:33.257 --> 00:19:35.259
Okay. ma'am. I'm gonna have to remove you.

330
00:19:49.106 --> 00:19:51.608
So. how exactly can you help?

331
00:19:52.442 --> 00:19:56.029
You'll be perfectly safe if you put down
that weapon and come with me now.

332
00:19:58.073 --> 00:19:59.157
Why should I believe you?

333
00:19:59.241 --> 00:20:00.409
You don't have much choice.

334
00:20:00.492 --> 00:20:02.995
because if you stay in here armed.
you could get hurt.

335
00:20:04.079 --> 00:20:06.081
Open the door then. Go. open.

336
00:20:06.164 --> 00:20:09.001
Update your hostage list.
Someone else just walked in.

337
00:20:11.336 --> 00:20:13.046
- Eyes up!
- Back off!

338
00:20:13.547 --> 00:20:15.257
- No?
- Down!

339
00:20:15.340 --> 00:20:17.926
- Put the gun down!
- You could have just walked out with me.

340
00:20:18.010 --> 00:20:21.054
- Put the gun down!
- And what? Back into the Park. huh?

341
00:20:21.138 --> 00:20:22.306
Why would I want that?

342
00:20:22.389 --> 00:20:23.557
Put the gun down!

343
00:20:23.640 --> 00:20:25.517
I told you to back off!

344
00:20:28.187 --> 00:20:29.771
- Stop moving!
- They'll kill you.

345
00:20:29.855 --> 00:20:32.316
- Put the gun down! Now!
- I'm gonna shoot!

346
00:20:32.900 --> 00:20:34.693
I'm not fucking joking. I'll shoot!

347
00:20:34.776 --> 00:20:36.320
Put the gun down!

348
00:21:18.904 --> 00:21:19.905
Déjà vu.

349
00:21:19.988 --> 00:21:22.533
Come. hands up. Up. on your head.

350
00:21:28.705 --> 00:21:29.998
Come on. Cheer up.

351
00:21:30.666 --> 00:21:33.293
I'd take prison any day
over dating Roddy Ho.

352
00:21:33.377 --> 00:21:34.378
Fuck you!

353
00:21:38.173 --> 00:21:41.051
Lima. Golf 5-7 to control.
We've apprehended the suspect.

354
00:21:42.302 --> 00:21:43.887
We're bringing her in now. Over.

355
00:21:47.474 --> 00:21:49.268
You knew that was going to happen.
didn't you?

356
00:21:50.310 --> 00:21:51.520
Yeah.

357
00:21:52.020 --> 00:21:53.772
And like I said. she's just a kid.

358
00:21:54.523 --> 00:21:55.858
She was never gonna shoot ya.

359
00:21:56.650 --> 00:21:58.652
Well. it didn't feel like that.

360
00:22:02.072 --> 00:22:03.323
Come on.

361
00:22:04.867 --> 00:22:06.451
I'll buy you a lemonade.

362
00:22:10.581 --> 00:22:11.790
Take the edge off.

363
00:22:15.169 --> 00:22:17.379
More will die than in the first attack.

364
00:22:18.005 --> 00:22:19.298
All of them will die.

365
00:22:34.646 --> 00:22:36.899
The hour's nearly up.
We need to get them out of there.

366
00:22:36.982 --> 00:22:38.650
Yeah. but calmly. We don't want panic.

367
00:22:39.193 --> 00:22:41.904
They might already be inside
dressed as mourners.

368
00:22:41.987 --> 00:22:42.988
It's what I'd do.

369
00:22:43.071 --> 00:22:44.448
I still don't have a gun.

370
00:22:45.032 --> 00:22:46.408
Don't worry. We've still got ours.

371
00:22:46.491 --> 00:22:48.035
How'd that work out for Gimball?

372
00:22:50.329 --> 00:22:56.210
Till we have built Jerusalem

373
00:22:56.710 --> 00:23:03.175
In England's green and pleasant land

374
00:23:11.141 --> 00:23:15.354
William Blake wrote those words
of promise over 200 years ago.

375
00:23:15.437 --> 00:23:19.608
but they continue to inspire
and comfort today.

376
00:23:20.150 --> 00:23:22.486
But for more contemporary wisdom

377
00:23:22.569 --> 00:23:24.780
that might give solace
to our younger mourners.

378
00:23:24.863 --> 00:23:29.493
I reach for the words
of Dominic Toretto in Furious 7.

379
00:23:31.537 --> 00:23:37.751
"They say to live in the hearts
of those we leave behind is not to die."

380
00:23:39.086 --> 00:23:41.922
The lesson I take from both those sages.

381
00:23:42.005 --> 00:23:43.966
separated though they are by centuries.

382
00:23:44.049 --> 00:23:47.302
is that while London might not
be "Londerful" today.

383
00:23:47.386 --> 00:23:50.055
it will be "Londerful" tomorrow
if we channel--

384
00:23:50.138 --> 00:23:52.975
Yeah. right. Everyone. up.

385
00:23:53.058 --> 00:23:55.769
We need you to leave this building
as quickly as possible. please.

386
00:23:55.853 --> 00:23:57.729
- What's going on?
- Sorry. we're MI5. I don't have…

387
00:23:57.813 --> 00:23:59.481
- Can you show them your… the badge?
- Stand back.

388
00:23:59.565 --> 00:24:01.483
Yeah. maybe you should've started
with taking them aside.

389
00:24:01.567 --> 00:24:04.903
Everyone. intelligence has come to light

390
00:24:04.987 --> 00:24:07.322
that means it's best for you
to leave right now.

391
00:24:07.406 --> 00:24:09.658
So please do so
from the back of the building.

392
00:24:09.741 --> 00:24:12.828
No need to panic. everyone.
Just slowly. safely exit the building.

393
00:24:12.911 --> 00:24:14.580
Everyone. now please! Come on!

394
00:24:14.663 --> 00:24:15.998
I mean it. now! Get out!

395
00:24:16.582 --> 00:24:18.250
Everyone. come on. now! Please!

396
00:24:20.169 --> 00:24:22.004
What the fuck happened to "calmly"?

397
00:24:22.588 --> 00:24:25.007
Hang on. What the hell is going on?
I'd only just started my eulogy.

398
00:24:25.090 --> 00:24:28.760
Apologies. sir. I know. but we need to
get you to leave the building now.

399
00:24:28.844 --> 00:24:30.304
- Whoa. whoa. All right.
- Hang on. Is it a fire?

400
00:24:30.387 --> 00:24:32.431
- No. there's not a fire.
- Then why did he hit the alarm?

401
00:24:32.514 --> 00:24:34.558
- Yeah. good question.
- It's a security threat. okay?

402
00:24:34.641 --> 00:24:36.977
- A security threat has come to light.
- What kind of threat?

403
00:24:37.060 --> 00:24:40.063
Libyan operatives are extorting
the government for £100 million.

404
00:24:40.147 --> 00:24:41.148
I can't hear you.

405
00:24:41.231 --> 00:24:43.817
Sorry. Can someone turn
that fucking thing off. please?

406
00:24:55.162 --> 00:24:57.581
In under a minute.
we have to pay £100 million

407
00:24:58.165 --> 00:25:00.209
or a place of worship
is gonna be attacked.

408
00:25:00.292 --> 00:25:03.462
and we have reason to believe
it could be here. Please. just believe…

409
00:25:03.545 --> 00:25:05.547
Thank God. Did you get that?

410
00:25:05.631 --> 00:25:07.716
Yes. You have reason to believe
this place could be attacked.

411
00:25:07.799 --> 00:25:10.219
- Yeah. so please. let's leave now.
- But you don't know for sure?

412
00:25:10.302 --> 00:25:12.387
Intelligence is never 100% certain. sir.

413
00:25:12.471 --> 00:25:14.765
What percentage would you put
on this piece of intelligence?

414
00:25:14.848 --> 00:25:16.391
- That really matter?
- Yes. I'm the Mayor of London.

415
00:25:16.475 --> 00:25:17.893
If an attack was highly likely.

416
00:25:17.976 --> 00:25:19.186
- I should've been informed.
- Well…

417
00:25:20.771 --> 00:25:21.772
Fuck. Not now.

418
00:25:27.361 --> 00:25:29.154
Look. it really is not the time
to argue about protocol.

419
00:25:29.238 --> 00:25:31.740
- Get Whelan on the line.
- Seriously. I need him to leave now.

420
00:25:35.702 --> 00:25:37.037
We can get them outside.

421
00:25:39.414 --> 00:25:40.916
The mayor is still here.

422
00:25:40.999 --> 00:25:42.751
I was cheated out of killing him before.

423
00:25:43.335 --> 00:25:45.045
- We get him first.
- Okay.

424
00:25:46.505 --> 00:25:48.173
You distract his security team.

425
00:25:52.511 --> 00:25:53.971
- What's your name?
- My…

426
00:25:54.054 --> 00:25:55.681
- River Cartwright.
- River?

427
00:25:55.764 --> 00:25:56.849
Yes.

428
00:25:56.932 --> 00:25:58.475
Claude. I'm here with River Cartwright.

429
00:25:58.559 --> 00:26:01.395
who's crashed into the memorial service
babbling something about a Libyan attack

430
00:26:01.478 --> 00:26:03.272
that none of my agents
seem to know anything about.

431
00:26:03.355 --> 00:26:04.356
Right.

432
00:26:05.107 --> 00:26:08.694
Well. first of all.
apologies on that. Zafar. Apologies.

433
00:26:10.779 --> 00:26:14.032
You should have been
kept in the loop on that.

434
00:26:14.116 --> 00:26:17.411
although in our defense.
it has been a very fast-moving situation.

435
00:26:19.621 --> 00:26:20.831
- Yes.
- Was there gonna be an attack

436
00:26:20.914 --> 00:26:21.915
on the service or not?

437
00:26:21.999 --> 00:26:23.166
Yes. yes. there was.

438
00:26:23.250 --> 00:26:25.294
To be honest.
we had no intelligence either way

439
00:26:25.377 --> 00:26:26.962
that you were specifically under threat.

440
00:26:27.045 --> 00:26:29.923
Of course. if-if we had received
that information. then… then…

441
00:26:30.007 --> 00:26:31.508
- then we would've intervened.
- Now hang on.

442
00:26:31.592 --> 00:26:34.261
you did intervene. I'm stood in front
of a load of your agents.

443
00:26:34.344 --> 00:26:37.097
Would you mind putting
Cartwright on for me. please?

444
00:26:42.102 --> 00:26:43.395
Wants to speak to you.

445
00:26:45.272 --> 00:26:47.482
- Sir.
- What the fuck are you doing?

446
00:26:48.192 --> 00:26:50.110
We thought the attack was
gonna be at Abbotsfield.

447
00:26:50.194 --> 00:26:51.653
Yeah. well. we paid them the money.

448
00:26:52.279 --> 00:26:55.032
There's not gonna be an attack anywhere.
And certainly not at Abbotsfield.

449
00:26:58.744 --> 00:26:59.745
Get out!

450
00:27:33.237 --> 00:27:34.780
Have you actually ever used one of those?

451
00:27:34.863 --> 00:27:36.949
You had the better angle.

452
00:27:38.200 --> 00:27:39.201
Are you okay?

453
00:27:44.456 --> 00:27:45.916
Fuck.

454
00:27:47.000 --> 00:27:48.168
Shit.

455
00:27:52.172 --> 00:27:54.216
- How many have you got left?
- Enough.

456
00:27:56.552 --> 00:27:57.761
Shit.

457
00:28:00.222 --> 00:28:02.558
Just give him what he wants.
For fuck's sake. give him what he wants.

458
00:28:02.641 --> 00:28:04.518
I want to get out of the country.

459
00:28:04.601 --> 00:28:06.311
- The deal still stands.
- What deal?

460
00:28:06.395 --> 00:28:07.938
With MI5. Safe passage.

461
00:28:08.021 --> 00:28:09.898
You're kidding. right?
You're not getting safe passage.

462
00:28:09.982 --> 00:28:11.859
You broke that deal when you opened fire.

463
00:28:11.942 --> 00:28:13.944
- Don't say that to him.
- Well. I'm not gonna lie.

464
00:28:14.027 --> 00:28:15.112
I'd really rather you lied.

465
00:28:15.195 --> 00:28:17.531
Let me out of here or I shoot your mayor!

466
00:28:17.614 --> 00:28:20.367
- No. not happening.
- Yes. otherwise he'll shoot him.

467
00:28:21.326 --> 00:28:24.079
Do not aim for his neck.
We've established you're a shit shot.

468
00:28:24.162 --> 00:28:25.539
There's other parts of him to aim for.

469
00:28:25.622 --> 00:28:28.083
I'm going to walk out of here
and I'm taking him with me.

470
00:28:28.166 --> 00:28:29.793
- No. we can't let you do that.
- Yes. you can.

471
00:28:29.877 --> 00:28:31.420
Can you stop fucking contradicting me?

472
00:28:31.503 --> 00:28:33.839
Yeah. I will if you stop escalating
a dangerous situation.

473
00:28:33.922 --> 00:28:36.133
- I'm on top of it. I know what I'm doing.
- We've got a madman

474
00:28:36.216 --> 00:28:38.427
pointing a gun at a hostage.
I say let him do what he wants.

475
00:28:38.510 --> 00:28:40.804
You see. that's why you're never gonna
get out of Slough House.

476
00:28:47.436 --> 00:28:49.229
Shit. Shit.

477
00:28:49.313 --> 00:28:51.231
Where… Where did you come from?

478
00:28:52.441 --> 00:28:54.776
I approached him very. very quietly.

479
00:28:56.361 --> 00:28:59.531
You two… You two staged your argument
to give him cover.

480
00:28:59.615 --> 00:29:01.950
I get that. I get that. I get that now.

481
00:29:02.451 --> 00:29:03.452
Fuck.

482
00:29:04.912 --> 00:29:05.913
Yeah. yeah.

483
00:29:06.914 --> 00:29:08.207
It's unorthodox. yeah.

484
00:29:08.290 --> 00:29:12.002
But you just gotta
think outside the box sometimes.

485
00:29:12.586 --> 00:29:13.587
Don't you?

486
00:29:15.339 --> 00:29:16.340
Yeah.

487
00:29:22.846 --> 00:29:24.139
We've accounted for all the Libyans.

488
00:29:24.223 --> 00:29:26.975
Two were shot at Abbotsfield.
and Lamb apprehended Tara.

489
00:29:27.059 --> 00:29:28.060
What was he doing there?

490
00:29:28.143 --> 00:29:29.144
I don't know. ma'am.

491
00:29:32.564 --> 00:29:35.108
We pay up and they attack anyway.
What a shit show.

492
00:29:35.692 --> 00:29:36.944
You didn't have a choice.

493
00:29:38.445 --> 00:29:41.615
When they pick over the bones of this.
you'll be exonerated. ma'am.

494
00:29:44.243 --> 00:29:45.577
London rules will kick in.

495
00:29:46.328 --> 00:29:47.454
